---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Canton Fair Buyer Checklist"
  description="A practical Canton Fair buyer checklist for overseas visitors preparing phases, registration, hotel location, booth visits, and supplier follow-up."
  canonical="/tools/canton-fair-buyer-checklist/"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="hub-hero">
      <div class="page-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">Buyer tool</span>
        <h1>Canton Fair Buyer Checklist</h1>
        <p>
          Use this checklist to prepare your Canton Fair visit before arriving in Guangzhou and to keep supplier meetings
          organized during the fair.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hub-visual" aria-label="Canton Fair buyer checklist preview">
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">P</span><div><strong>Phase</strong><p>Match products to the correct fair phase.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">ID</span><div><strong>Badge</strong><p>Prepare registration and business cards.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">Q</span><div><strong>Questions</strong><p>Use the same questions with each supplier.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Before you travel</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Confirm the fair phase that matches your product category.</li>
          <li>Prepare buyer registration details, passport information, and business cards.</li>
          <li>Book a hotel with practical access to the Pazhou exhibition complex.</li>
          <li>List your target products, target price range, and expected order quantity.</li>
          <li>Prepare a simple booth note template for every supplier conversation.</li>
          <li>Decide which suppliers need sample requests, quotation follow-up, or factory visit discussion.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Supplier meeting checklist</h2>
        <table class="simple-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Question</th>
              <th>Why it matters</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>What is the MOQ?</td>
              <td>Checks whether the supplier fits your order size.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>What is included in the quote?</td>
              <td>Prevents confusion around packaging, accessories, and trade terms.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>How long do samples and production take?</td>
              <td>Helps you compare realistic timelines.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Can you provide certificates or test reports?</td>
              <td>Important for regulated products and market requirements.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2>Related guides</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/canton-fair/">Canton Fair Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/canton-fair-first-time-buyer-guide/">Canton Fair Guide for First-Time Overseas Buyers</a></li>
          <li><a href="/tools/supplier-comparison-sheet/">Supplier Comparison Sheet</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="notice-box">
          <h2>Fair day habit</h2>
          <p>Write notes after every booth visit. Supplier details blur together quickly in a large exhibition hall.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
